Locale Class

1. What is Locale class in Java? Why is it important in internationalization? Important methods of Locale class?
-->The Locale class (java.util.Locale) represents a specific language and country/region.

It is mainly used for Internationalization (i18n), allowing applications to display language, currency, dates, and numbers according to the user's region.

Import

import java.util.Locale;

Example

Locale locale = new Locale("en", "US");
System.out.println(locale);



Important Methods :
| Method                  | Description            |
| ----------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `getDefault()`          | Returns default locale |
| `getLanguage()`         | Returns language code  |
| `getCountry()`          | Returns country code   |
| `getDisplayLanguage()`  | Returns language name  |
| `getDisplayCountry()`   | Returns country name   |
| `getAvailableLocales()` | Returns all locales    |








2. What are the predefined Locale constants in Java? (Locale.US, Locale.UK, etc.)
-->Answer:
Some predefined constants are:
      Locale.US
      Locale.UK
      Locale.CANADA
      Locale.CANADA_FRENCH
      Locale.FRANCE
      Locale.GERMANY
      Locale.ITALY
      Locale.JAPAN
      Locale.CHINA
      Locale.KOREA
      Locale.ROOT

Example:
    System.out.println(Locale.US);
    System.out.println(Locale.UK);

Output:
    en_US
    en_GB



3. How to get all available locales?
-->Answer:
      import java.util.Locale;
      
      public class Main {
          public static void main(String[] args) {
              Locale[] locales = Locale.getAvailableLocales();
      
              for (Locale l : locales) {
                  System.out.println(l);
              }
          }
      }
